User Story
As a security-conscious platform team
I want the Agent Portal User Profile function to use Easy Auth for callers and Managed Identity for Dataverse
So that we can remove CRM client secrets and function keys while keeping the API secure

Acceptance Criteria
Function app uses Easy Auth (Entra ID) to protect inbound requests
HTTP trigger uses AuthorizationLevel.Anonymous (Easy Auth handles auth)
Function connects to Dataverse using Managed Identity (no CRM_CLIENT_SECRET)
CRM_CLIENT_ID and CRM_CLIENT_SECRET are removed from app settings and pipeline variables
Function app managed identity is registered as a Dataverse Application User with the required security role
Authenticated user identity is read from Easy Auth claims (not only from query parameters)
Existing getSOReqForEappSSO behavior still returns the same user profile data for valid requests
Tasks
Enable Easy Auth on the function app
Update function code to use Managed Identity for Dataverse connection
Update ARM template and pipeline variables
Create Dataverse Application User for managed identity
Test end-to-end with a valid Bearer token
